step_data.thought:
I've been comparing different map styles by cycling through all four available options (Standard, CyclOSM, ÖPNVKarte, and Humanitarian) and zooming in to better see urban details. I'm currently viewing the Humanitarian style and have zoomed in twice.

To complete a thorough comparison, I should continue zooming in more to reach a level where urban details are clearly visible. This will allow me to properly assess which map style provides the most detail for urban areas.

Let me zoom in a few more times to get to a street-level view where urban details like buildings, points of interest, and street networks are clearly visible.
